sections.comments: Visit https://cnrs.ubc.ca/fall2020courses/ for information on course delivery. If this course is full or blocked, please register in the wait list section.CLST 332 is equivalent to ARTH 332. If this course is full, students can register in the equivalent section. ARTH 332 will apply towards Classical, Near Eastern and Religious Studies program requirements in the same way as CLST 332. Please contact the CNERS undergraduate advisor with any questions at cners.advising@ubc.ca.Students who have received credit for CLST 330 may not also receive credit for CLST 331 or 332.

description: The visual culture of the ancient Roman world from the 8th century BCE to the 4th century CE.
